        Parameters:
        languageCode - The language code as LANGUAGE_COUNTY_VARIANT
        name - The name of the language (Should be the foreign name).

      • getAllLanguages

        @Transactional(readOnly=true)
Map<String,String> getAllLanguages()
        Returns all languages for the client.
        Returns:
        Map of all language codes with their names.

      • getAvailableLanguages

        @Transactional(readOnly=true)
Collection<Language> getAvailableLanguages()
        This method returns all available languages. In contrast to getUsedLanguages() it will not include an inactive language of the current user. Will maintain the languages itself and not use the database.
        Returns:
        All languages which currently have at least one active localization.
        See Also:
        getUsedLanguages()

      • getCountries

        List<Country> getCountries(Locale locale)

        Returns a list of all countries in the database.

      • getLanguages

        List<Language> getLanguages()
        Returns:
        All known languages. Includes also languages, there is currently no localization active.

      • getTimeZones

        List<SimplifiedTimeZone> getTimeZones()

        Returns:
        The available list of time zones.

      • getUsedLanguages

        @Transactional(readOnly=true)
Collection<Language> getUsedLanguages()
        This method returns all available languages plus the language of the current user. For only retrieving the available languages use getAvailableLanguages() Will use the database only for getting the language of the current user.
        Returns:
        All languages which currently have at least one active localization. Includes the current users language, even if there is no localization for it.
        See Also:
        getAvailableLanguages()

      • isAvailableLanguage

        @Transactional(readOnly=true)
boolean isAvailableLanguage(Locale locale)
        Test whether the language of the locale belongs to the available languages.
        Parameters:
        locale - the locale to test
        Returns:
        true if the language of the locale is among the available languages
